PMarrayData.PositioningScript:
var detectorSize = 33.2
var half_detectorSize = detectorSize / 2

var num_of_SiPMs = 8       // along one direction
var active_area_side = 3
var extra_margin = 0.1  //  one can assume this value from the specified SiPMs pitch: from http://www.sensl.com/downloads/ds/PB-ArraySMT.pdf
var half_not_active_area_side = 0.42 + 0.17/2 + extra_margin  // SiPMs pitch = 4.21  -> See http://sensl.com/downloads/ds/DS-MicroCseries.pdf and http://www.sensl.com/downloads/ds/PB-ArraySMT.pdf

var SiPMSide = active_area_side +  half_not_active_area_side * 2       // Sensl 30035 (array 4x4 SiPMs)

var detectorMargin = (detectorSize - (num_of_SiPMs) * SiPMSide) /2 

for(var y=0; y<8;y++)
for (var x=0; x<8; x++) 
             PM(-half_detectorSize + detectorMargin + SiPMSide/2 + x *  SiPMSide , 
              -half_detectorSize + detectorMargin + SiPMSide/2 + y *  SiPMSide, 0, 0)
